<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / Business and the Law: Higher salaries - Legal Briefs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Salaries for assistant solicitors in London have risen strongly, according
to legal recruitment consultants Quarry Dougall. For firms with more than 25
partners, solicitors qualified for four years can earn up to Pounds 52,000 a
year and those qualified for eight years, Pounds 83,500.
