<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / DTI hospitality spending rises
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The efforts made to promote British business by the Department of Trade and
Industry are resulting in sharply higher official hospitality bills.
DTI figures published last week show that the total amount spent on official
hospitality reached nearly Pounds 700,000 in 1993-94 - up from less than
Pounds 400,000 three years earlier.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
