<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / First-day covers scheme welcomed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Office of Fair Trading has welcomed a Royal Mail plan to assist
independent producers of first-day covers.
Mr Anthony Buckingham, managing director of Benham, an independent first-day
cover producer in Folkestone, Kent, said he had complained to the OFT that
Royal Mail was charging almost face value for stamps while the Philatelic
Bureau, Royal Mail's in-house operation, had to pay only the production cost
of stamps for its covers.
Now the Royal Mail plans a scheme to enable independent producers to claim a
rebate on stamps affixed and cancelled on their first-day covers.
