<HEADLINE>
FT  01 NOV 94 / World Trade News: Taiwan's trade deficit jumps
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURA TYSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Taiwan's trade deficit with Europe rose to Dollars 2.36bn during the first
nine months of this year, compared to Dollars 752m during the same period
last year, sparking concern among the island's trade authorities. Exports to
Europe from January to September fell 3.7 per cent to Dollars 9.25bn, while
imports climbed 12.1 per cent to Dollars 11.61bn. Germany was Taiwan's
biggest trading partner.
</TEXT>
