FT  31 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Charnos
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CHARNOS pre-tax losses jumped to Pounds 2.32m (Pounds 667,000) in the six
months to June 25 on sales of Pounds 24.9m (Pounds 22.7m). Losses per share
were 78.2p (22.96p). The company, which makes hosiery and lingerie, said
budgeted sales for the final weeks of the year should result in a pre-tax
profit comparable to last time's Pounds 5.2m. It could not make a firm
prediction because of uncertain factors.
