<HEADLINE>
FT  31 OCT 94 / Company News This Week: J Sainsbury - Other companies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
J Sainsbury: The UK's largest food retailer reports interim results on
Wednesday, and Kwik Save, the biggest discount chain, reports its finals on
Thursday. Pre-tax profits forecasts for Sainsbury range from Pounds 430m to
about Pounds 460m, with the consensus at around Pounds 445m - a 7 per cent
increase from a restated Pounds 417m last year. Forecasts for Kwik Save are
concentrated around Pounds 130m, an increase of only 3 per cent. Kwik Save
is suffering from the increased competition in the market, which is eroding
its price advantage over the superstore groups.
