<HEADLINE>
FT  31 OCT 94 / Business Travel: Bombay chaos
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Overcrowding, breakdowns and a shortage of funds have turned rail commuting
in and around Bombay into a daily nightmare.  The 2,000 trains on Bombay's
suburban network trundle nearly 5m people to work each day.  Frustration has
turned to violence five times in the past four months, with commuters
wrecking property.
The authorities plan to use longer trains and phase out level-crossings. But
raising funds will be difficult.  'We may have to consider approaching the
European markets, through the finance ministry, for cheaper funds,' said an
official.
